Stage your changes

git add .


. stages all changes (new, modified, deleted files).

Commit your changes with a message

git commit -m "Your commit message here"


Replace "Your commit message here" with a description of your changes.

Push your changes to the remote repository

git push origin main


origin = name of your remote repository.

main = branch you are pushing to.

âœ… Optional: Check status anytime:

git status